title: Dollar Drops Ahead of Fed Minutes
text:
The dollar fell to a nearly three-week low Thursday, as investors cut positions in the currency ahead of the release of minutes from the Federal Reserveâ€™s latest meeting.
The Wall Street Journal Dollar Index, which gauges the buck against a basket of 16 currencies, was recently down 0.3% at 87.66, its lowest level since Sept. 17.
